{
  "stem": "10272.8",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They want to see this story involved in some kind of entertainment, like, like, if Spielberg would show only what happened in Cracow with this-- with this-- with this how Jews were killed and how they suffered, they wouldn't be such a big success.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He managed to put in some kind of a story, a human story, that was appealing to some people and entertaining.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they went to see two hours and sit in the movie and watch it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Otherwise, they wouldn't go to watch it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now I found somebody.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's a girl here in Staten Island.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She's working on such a story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If I manage to make this story, then I can-- maybe in a few years, I can produce a real story which people will see-- oh, I saw something, which I learned something.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This would be both educational and historical, based on historical facts.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they will also get-- have fun in seeing something most interesting.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Otherwise, people will never be willing to sit and watch it on TV or in a movie-- my story.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because it's just a, a story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I would like to thank-- to say-- to express my deep appreciation and gratitude to all of you who are working with these Holocaust survivors in bringing their story so that never can be forgotten what happened.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even if you are not dealing specifically on the other side of the-- of the coin, which is how it could happen.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this is also a very noble goal, what you are doing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Mr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Steven Spielberg himself, who, who donated all this money-- this financing for all these projects, I myself give a token of appreciation by sending him my painted in, in, in oil color, his portrait, for which he sent me a nice letter thanking me for my gift to him.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is a picture of my father, Mendel Jacobovitz, Jacobovitz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The picture was taken in Chicago, Illinois, when he came from America to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he put this picture on his passport-- American passport.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's about-- after World War I.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It could be approximately 1919 or 1920.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On this picture, we see myself, Emil Jacoby.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that time, I was called Emil Jacobovitz, and Betty, at that time called Bertina Bercu.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was in the-- 1951, when we-- at the time that we were engaged.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was in, in Harduf.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Israel.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This picture was taken in April the 3rd, 1952, during our wedding ceremony in Ra'anana, Israel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On this picture is myself, Emil Jacoby, and Betty Bercu.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This picture was taken approximately in 1960 in Israel after was-- Rachel and Nahama were born.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we see on this picture myself, Emil Jacoby, and my wife, Betty Jacoby, and the parents of my wife.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the-- was the father-in-law, Bercu-- Julius-- and the mother-in-law, Esther Bercu.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This picture was taken at the B'nai Jeshuron Synagogue in Staten Island in October, 1992, during the bat mitzvah party of our granddaughter, Sheera Borenstein.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On this picture, we see myself, my wife, on the other side, Betty, our, our son-in-law, Gabe Borenstein, and our daughter, Rachel Borenstein, with our grandchildren, with our daughter-in-law, Nahama Cohen.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Daughter-in-law Nahama.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Daughter.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, daughter, Nahama.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And our grandchildren, [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Estee ?] Borenstein and Yossi Borenstein.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There's [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maya ?] Cohen and Sheera Borenstein.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This picture was also taken during the bat mitzvah in 1992, during the bat mitzvah of Sheera Borenstein.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you have all the six grandchildren on this picture.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "From right to left, there is [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Maya ?] Cohen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There is [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Estee ?] Borenstein, Yossi Borenstein, [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Liat ?] Cohen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there's Oren Cohen and [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Estee ?] Borenstein.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "On this picture, we are together, me and my wife, Betty, visiting Auschwitz in 1987, Auschwitz Concentration Camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The, the, the place is Birkenau, actually.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Next to Auschwitz, there's another camp called Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This picture was taken in 1988, in Manhattan, New York, when our-- when my son, Jirka Kuchar, came to visit us from Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
